This, however, plays an important role in German considerations.
Did Germany's relations with the US deteriorate when Germany abstained from voting on Palestine in the event of both important decisions?
I think there is a great deal of understanding for the German attitude in Europe and even in the US.
That's why I don't think it was as dramatic a fracture as Libya.
Perhaps even Germany will earn some respect.
